WEBVTT

04:09.730 --> 04:14.475
walking up those steps, feels like that rocky movie, if you know what I mean.

04:14.515 --> 04:18.219
Get yourself, get yourself ready.

04:20.702 --> 04:29.131
Good morning, I'm just a, all right.

04:29.272 --> 04:30.533
Okay, good to see everyone.

04:32.275 --> 04:38.802
So last week, Ale talked about a message and I'm hoping

04:39.106 --> 04:40.468
We all remember what it was.

04:41.169 --> 04:42.251
And it was a question.

04:43.052 --> 04:48.200
So for those of you who weren't here last week, the question was, why do we come to church?

04:49.002 --> 04:50.063
Why do we come to church?

04:51.225 --> 04:57.055
And this week, I asked him if he would allow me to tag on to that message.

04:57.155 --> 04:59.599
So I'm not trying to steal his thunder.

04:59.719 --> 05:00.480
He's right there.

05:00.500 --> 05:04.306
He inspired me to do it, in fact.

05:04.578 --> 05:09.985
And I asked him for permission because I really am not trying to get fired so soon.

05:10.025 --> 05:17.454
So just know that this is in addition to, or a follow up, the Edel's message.

05:17.775 --> 05:21.980
But the Lord put this on my heart after hearing his word on Sunday.

05:22.000 --> 05:22.781
So thank you, Edel.

05:24.403 --> 05:29.930
And I just wanted to add on one more thing on why we come to church.

05:29.950 --> 05:32.754
So before we do that, let's pray.

05:34.818 --> 05:48.337
Heavenly Father, we are so thankful that you are our cornerstone and that all of this that we get to hear today stems from what you did on the cross.

05:49.860 --> 05:55.708
And so, Lord, we want you to come to this room this morning.

05:56.549 --> 06:02.738
And I just ask that you just put me aside, and Lord, may your spirit come and just

06:03.970 --> 06:08.116
touch our hearts with this word that you prepared for us today.

06:08.237 --> 06:10.620
We just commit this day to you in Jesus' name.

06:10.640 --> 06:12.083
Amen.

06:12.103 --> 06:13.665
All right, so why do we come to church?

06:16.129 --> 06:24.662
Well, one thing I love about church over the years, I've found people who kind of share my various interests, right?

06:24.802 --> 06:29.810
I can name, you know, I can try to name everyone, but for the sake of

06:29.954 --> 06:36.905
You know, I can't name everyone, but for the sake of a concrete example, I'm gonna try and name a few, right?

06:37.265 --> 06:42.172
So if I ever wanna go on a hike, there's Alex Romanov and Gilbert.

06:43.394 --> 06:46.639
If I wanna come home with some bugs, I would ask Jeff.

06:49.303 --> 06:50.305
There's Disneyland.

06:51.847 --> 06:52.668
You know who you are.

06:53.730 --> 06:54.411
Raise your hands.

06:55.593 --> 06:59.058
There's, you know, we're riding mountain bikes, computers.

06:59.330 --> 07:01.736
baseball, organic bananas.

07:03.300 --> 07:05.866
So, you know, Emma Fuller knows this.

07:07.029 --> 07:09.034
Just all sorts of interests, right?

07:10.076 --> 07:17.394
And I don't expect everyone or anyone to be as enthusiastic as Mike Weiss.

07:17.602 --> 07:19.525
or Eddie about lawn care.

07:19.565 --> 07:21.849
So when I need something, I go to them.

07:21.949 --> 07:22.490
I just know.

07:22.510 --> 07:23.271
I just know.

07:23.291 --> 07:25.394
I just consult the experts.

07:25.474 --> 07:27.117
But these are all varied interests.

07:27.197 --> 07:27.898
And I'm thankful.

07:28.199 --> 07:29.761
Over the years, I've come to this church.

07:29.881 --> 07:30.743
I know who to talk to.

07:31.223 --> 07:34.028
And it's the fabric that weaves us together.

07:34.589 --> 07:37.954
But one last one, off the menu.

07:38.014 --> 07:40.498
You won't see this posted anywhere on our website.

07:40.518 --> 07:42.221
But I will make a plug for Gabriel.

07:42.621 --> 07:45.746
He has the unofficial eating ministry.

07:46.114 --> 07:50.538
So just know that if you know who to ask, there is an eating ministry.

07:51.199 --> 07:56.064
And I'm seeing some smiling faces because we know it's there.

07:56.384 --> 08:03.551
But I say that all to say that this family of God that we have is so woven together.

08:04.492 --> 08:14.962
And I consider myself fortunate that when I come to church, the lion's blur between my heavenly family and who I consider my earthly family.

08:15.874 --> 08:25.944
But for those who haven't been coming here a long time, that might seem strange that everyone here feels or seems so deeply connected.

08:26.745 --> 08:29.488
But that barely really scratches the surface.

08:29.608 --> 08:32.050
And for those of us who've been here, we know that.

08:34.072 --> 08:40.319
And so we know that SRVBC isn't just a social club, right?

08:40.959 --> 08:43.442
It's not simply here to fulfill

08:43.682 --> 08:45.505
my personal interests.

08:45.926 --> 08:47.228
It's much deeper than that.

08:47.368 --> 08:57.043
And so in addition to all the reasons Edel shared last week, I just wanted to pose one more thing of why we come to church.

08:57.784 --> 09:00.368
And that's the title of our message today.

09:00.849 --> 09:03.573
It's, therefore, let us run.

09:04.355 --> 09:07.740
So the reason I wanted to pose for us this morning is simple.

09:07.760 --> 09:09.382
It's for us to run together.

09:10.564 --> 09:11.666
So let's read for

09:11.810 --> 09:13.232
from our main verse today.

09:13.272 --> 09:18.217
It's Hebrews chapter 12, verse one and two.

09:19.058 --> 09:24.805
And you can keep it up there for a little bit because we're just gonna stay in this verse pretty much the entire time.

09:27.208 --> 09:29.871
Hebrews chapter 12, verse one and two.

09:30.451 --> 09:39.602
It goes, therefore, since we are surrounded by such a great cloud of witnesses, let us throw off everything that hinders

09:39.714 --> 09:48.148
and the sin that so easily entangles and let us run the race with perseverance marked out for us.

09:50.171 --> 09:56.282
Fixing our eyes on Jesus, the pioneer and perfecter of our faith.

09:56.302 --> 09:58.065
So we're going to spend a little bit of time.

09:58.125 --> 09:59.447
It's a media verse.

10:00.889 --> 10:03.794
And we're going to start with the first word, therefore.

10:04.994 --> 10:06.896
So let me talk about this word therefore.

10:07.276 --> 10:08.778
So there's a major context.

10:08.858 --> 10:22.631
It's really easy to miss when you're reading this verse because you go right into the meat of it, which is, you know, the great cloud of witnesses, the sin that easily entangles, the race, the run, but there's that one word right in front of it, which is therefore.

10:24.192 --> 10:30.238
And any time you read that word in the New Testament books, it's good to pay attention to understand, right?

10:30.338 --> 10:34.322
Because it's good to know the four that was,

10:34.402 --> 10:38.869
or what was before, before you to go to the there, which is ahead.

10:38.970 --> 10:40.713
And so we're gonna spend that time today.

10:41.454 --> 10:42.536
And so here's the context.

10:42.616 --> 10:46.142
The book of Hebrews was addressed to Jewish Christians.

10:46.783 --> 10:53.354
This group of Christians were faced with a lot of pressure to go back to their Jewish ways.

10:54.055 --> 10:57.240
So these were previous Jews who got saved.

10:58.142 --> 11:00.786
And as an early church, they were experiencing

11:00.866 --> 11:02.107
real consequences.

11:02.187 --> 11:06.932
They were starting to experience and live out what Christian life would be like.

11:07.453 --> 11:15.181
And those real consequences could have been public shame, financial loss, or even imprisonment, right?

11:15.241 --> 11:28.114
And so the author of Hebrews, we don't know who they are, who he is or she, wrote them this letter to encourage them to keep going and to keep growing in their faith.

11:28.322 --> 11:31.006
So that's what they did.

11:31.587 --> 11:37.556
And if you look at the chapter before Hebrews 11, this is what he did.

11:37.636 --> 11:39.459
He brought the big guns, right?

11:39.519 --> 11:42.604
So he talked about the heroes of the faith.

11:43.184 --> 11:54.802
So chapter 11, if you look at it, lists all that the Jews would have considered the big hitters or the who's who of the Jewish faith.

11:55.010 --> 12:00.679
And being converted to Jews, the audience would have grown up hearing all these great stories.

12:02.062 --> 12:07.591
You've got Abraham, Noah, Jacob, Moses, Joseph, and so on.

12:07.891 --> 12:09.494
And so that's what's going on here.

12:09.614 --> 12:17.487
Hebrews 11 is a setup to Hebrews 12, and that word therefore is that big transition moment.

12:18.108 --> 12:21.714
It was meant to connect the faithful of the past

12:22.434 --> 12:26.760
to the faithful of the present, the Hebrews, the church.

12:27.461 --> 12:32.768
And so therefore is an adverb for the language nerds, right?

12:33.229 --> 12:33.990
Had to look that up.

12:34.510 --> 12:43.182
It means as a result of, and so let's apply this today as the author meant for the Hebrews.

12:43.643 --> 12:47.768
We, the church, are a result of someone's great faith.

12:48.329 --> 12:50.051
And why do I come to church?

12:50.352 --> 12:52.114
Well, because someone brought me

12:52.226 --> 13:00.255
because someone prayed for me and I keep coming because someone poured in me the undeserved love of Christ.

13:00.635 --> 13:10.045
And because I was thirsty to know the deepest truth and I found it here and I knew that I would find something deeper here.

13:10.065 --> 13:22.098
And so I came, I came to church because someone here was willing and they know who they are to take the time to study the Word of God and share it with me

13:23.266 --> 13:29.372
And it doesn't matter if they were at the pulpit or helping me with a backyard project.

13:31.093 --> 13:33.976
That's why I came to church.

13:34.296 --> 13:44.927
And so therefore, we are here and it wasn't the coincidence because someone's faith encouraged us to be in these seats this morning.

13:48.290 --> 13:52.754
So our verse talked about a great cloud of witnesses who testified

13:52.834 --> 13:57.221
that the faithful will receive the promise of God's salvation.

13:58.743 --> 14:06.034
So you add the Abraham, the Moses, the Noah, so many more names of the faithful witnesses, right?

14:06.574 --> 14:07.876
You have them today, right?

14:08.037 --> 14:14.326
You have Silvia Aqual, Dean Allen, Bill Murray, Jim Hyde, many others past and present.

14:14.887 --> 14:17.691
And they all ran the race faithfully toward Jesus.

14:18.773 --> 14:19.333
And you know what?

14:19.654 --> 14:22.418
Now is the time for us to run ours.

14:23.330 --> 14:27.917
And that's the encouragement that we'll find in that one word, therefore.

14:28.198 --> 14:32.885
And so when I talk through the next verses, I'm gonna keep talking about therefore.

14:34.167 --> 14:41.519
And I know it's been 10 minutes now, or five minutes, and I've just stuck with the first word, but we're gonna move through pretty quickly after this.

14:42.600 --> 14:45.144
Trust me, I'm not trying to get fired.

14:46.487 --> 14:48.690
But Hebrews 12-1 describes

14:49.730 --> 14:51.572
this endurance race, right?

14:51.792 --> 14:54.896
We have the verse there, right?

14:55.797 --> 14:58.920
It is a race that requires perseverance.

15:00.062 --> 15:05.427
And so when running an endurance race, it's all about digging deep.

15:06.208 --> 15:10.213
And so the next part of our passage offers exactly that.

15:10.914 --> 15:14.918
It's an encouragement to dig deep because the race is long.

15:15.539 --> 15:18.482
And we need the motivation daily to keep going.

15:18.754 --> 15:21.057
So we're going to do that today.

15:21.538 --> 15:23.841
So let's dig deeper with a few more thoughts.

15:24.522 --> 15:31.951
So the first thought is, therefore, let us throw off everything that hinders.

15:35.636 --> 15:38.099
So I told the men this story a while back.

15:38.540 --> 15:41.444
I got saved around over 20 years ago.

15:42.365 --> 15:46.290
And at the time, I remember being so on fire for the Lord.

15:47.362 --> 15:54.033
And, you know, I just wanted to be the biggest blessing I could be as quickly as I possibly could, right?

15:54.053 --> 15:55.275
And I had this idea.

15:55.295 --> 15:58.399
And Jamie knows this when I have an idea.

15:58.440 --> 16:00.483
That's when trouble starts for me.

16:00.923 --> 16:02.005
So I had an idea.

16:03.447 --> 16:07.233
And I had a minor financial need at the time.

16:07.274 --> 16:11.680
And I got on my niece and I prayed for an answer.

16:13.243 --> 16:15.186
And I believed God would answer my prayer.

16:16.386 --> 16:18.608
if I helped him by buying a lottery ticket.

16:22.072 --> 16:25.075
So, I mean, I'm up here.

16:25.235 --> 16:26.396
I'm highly accountable.

16:27.077 --> 16:30.300
My intentions were completely earnest, right?

16:30.880 --> 16:34.664
My thinking was, so follow with me, young Christian, right?

16:36.025 --> 16:37.927
I would take 20% for myself.

16:39.869 --> 16:41.170
And I would give God 80%.

16:41.591 --> 16:43.353
That was the plan.

16:43.513 --> 16:44.754
I said, you know, Lord,

16:44.994 --> 16:46.896
You make this happen, 80%.

16:47.176 --> 16:51.340
And I felt, you know, at the time, totally justified.

16:51.360 --> 16:55.985
And I was so confident that I had the solution.

16:57.907 --> 17:02.751
But the Lord made it clear that was one of my first humbling experiences.

17:03.292 --> 17:09.978
You know, I had to learn to give up both my problems and my solutions to Him, 100% of it.

17:11.019 --> 17:13.682
I didn't need to keep 20% for myself.

17:13.986 --> 17:15.388
nor did he want 80%.

17:17.250 --> 17:30.288
And so when Jesus said in Matthew 19, 21, sell what you possess and give to the poor, and you will have treasure in heaven and come follow me, it wasn't about giving to the poor.

17:30.348 --> 17:41.042
It was about unburdening ourselves completely on this side of heaven so we can focus completely heavenbound or on Jesus.

17:42.274 --> 17:53.926
And so the message, the first message therefore let us throw off everything that hinders is about running light because we can't finish the race strong when we're weighed down.

17:55.587 --> 17:57.549
And notice that this is the first thought, right?

17:57.569 --> 18:02.995
So we're not, we are encouraged to do this at the start of the race and not towards the end.

18:03.055 --> 18:10.002
So you know, regardless of where we're at today, let's ask ourselves this question, what is holding us back?

18:12.034 --> 18:14.918
Are we afraid of letting the world pass us by?

18:14.958 --> 18:20.024
Are we afraid of giving something up to the Lord?

18:22.227 --> 18:29.495
We can look at all of his children and see how God never lets his faithful children down.

18:29.816 --> 18:34.942
And you know, I saw this first hand, and here comes the first therefore, right?

18:35.122 --> 18:39.508
I saw this first hand when my father-in-law Jim Hyde passed away.

18:39.888 --> 18:41.330
And for a moment there,

18:41.762 --> 18:46.768
I feared that his passing would be the start of a huge collapse in our family.

18:47.970 --> 18:52.456
Financially, practically, spiritually, you name it.

18:53.637 --> 18:55.900
Because it happened so fast and unexpectedly.

18:57.582 --> 19:01.688
But even Jim's death testified to God's faithfulness.

19:03.230 --> 19:09.618
Therefore, I am encouraged to unburden myself from all of these worries.

19:11.874 --> 19:17.841
So the second thought here is, therefore, let us untangle ourselves from sin.

19:18.161 --> 19:19.423
And you'll notice this.

19:19.603 --> 19:23.167
I'm just going section by section on this one verse.

19:24.609 --> 19:27.572
So untangle is an interesting choice of word.

19:27.612 --> 19:33.399
The original Greek translates to well-surrounding, the well-surrounding sin.

19:33.839 --> 19:36.282
And we are well-surrounded by sin.

19:37.203 --> 19:39.986
And when I talk to my kids about this idea,

19:40.898 --> 19:44.482
I explain it really simply, and it applies to me as well.

19:45.263 --> 19:50.488
But sin are the seeds that we plant in our hearts that grow into weeds.

19:52.831 --> 19:55.974
Weeds tangle us up.

19:55.994 --> 20:00.159
It's easy to spot a weed but difficult to catch a seed.

20:01.160 --> 20:05.084
And so therefore, we have to watch out for the seeds.

20:07.267 --> 20:10.450
So what seeds are being planted in our heart

20:10.530 --> 20:10.850
today.

20:12.493 --> 20:13.394
What do we watch?

20:14.275 --> 20:15.197
What do we let in?

20:15.277 --> 20:17.079
What do we listen to?

20:17.180 --> 20:18.962
Who do we spend time with?

20:19.463 --> 20:24.971
These are all seeds that get planted in our hearts and left unchecked.

20:26.173 --> 20:30.479
They sprout and you know what happens.

20:30.499 --> 20:33.663
Sylvia was an excellent weeder.

20:35.907 --> 20:38.290
When I would bring up a situation with her,

20:39.906 --> 20:46.452
I won't forget how expertly and lovingly she would point out those weeds in my life.

20:48.835 --> 20:50.376
And she would help me get untangled.

20:52.218 --> 20:59.405
And I'm so thankful that we continue to have people here who are willing to keep us accountable if we allow it.

21:00.446 --> 21:00.886
We need it.

21:02.648 --> 21:04.049
And so that's the second therefore.

21:06.511 --> 21:09.234
The third thought is therefore

21:09.698 --> 21:11.960
Let us run with perseverance.

21:12.161 --> 21:13.662
I told you we're gonna just keep going.

21:15.624 --> 21:18.467
Therefore, let us run with perseverance.

21:19.728 --> 21:23.192
And how can I not think about Dean with this one?

21:26.936 --> 21:34.643
There was this time when Dean and I, you know, we would practice for worship group on Wednesday nights.

21:35.604 --> 21:37.266
We stand right there.

21:39.458 --> 21:44.345
And Dean didn't need a microphone to sing.

21:46.268 --> 21:51.835
But there was one night when even I could hear it, he could barely sing.

21:55.300 --> 22:00.247
And it didn't sound good.

22:01.349 --> 22:02.370
You could hear his breath.

22:02.831 --> 22:03.612
It didn't sound right.

22:06.937 --> 22:07.858
And you know,

22:08.450 --> 22:12.516
Maybe a few minutes later, he just said he couldn't sing anymore.

22:12.937 --> 22:13.598
He passed out.

22:14.559 --> 22:16.923
And I know this for a fact.

22:17.063 --> 22:20.508
If we didn't call an ambulance, he would insist that he would keep singing.

22:24.214 --> 22:28.961
Every day, he wrote a devotion and shared it with whoever would want to hear it.

22:31.925 --> 22:35.250
And every single day, we would get a one call

22:36.034 --> 22:42.304
Or every single day that we would get the one call about his health, I would check and he would still share one.

22:46.630 --> 22:50.817
He would be writing in the hospital, trying to share an encouraging word.

22:54.562 --> 22:55.504
That's for severance.

22:57.186 --> 22:58.388
He persevered till the end.

23:01.092 --> 23:04.818
He reminded me of this one verse, Acts 20, 24.

23:05.346 --> 23:06.668
This is the life he lived.

23:07.329 --> 23:10.795
However, I consider my life worth nothing to me.

23:11.697 --> 23:17.006
My only aim is to finish the race and complete the task the Lord Jesus has given me.

23:17.567 --> 23:22.014
The task of testifying to the good news of God's grace.

23:22.876 --> 23:26.001
What a great example for us here, church.

23:29.607 --> 23:31.250
And I know we'll see him one day again.

23:34.786 --> 23:37.991
So here's the fourth and final thought.

23:39.593 --> 23:44.000
Therefore, let us fix our eyes on Jesus.

23:47.265 --> 23:53.754
You know, you can be the lightest, the strongest, and the most enduring runner.

23:55.717 --> 24:00.044
But if you're running the wrong way, you'll never finish the race.

24:02.127 --> 24:04.210
Jesus said he is the way.

24:05.858 --> 24:12.004
He marked out a race for each of us to run by living a life for us to follow.

24:14.646 --> 24:16.088
Bill Murray finished this race.

24:18.330 --> 24:25.917
He would always remind us that Jesus is the author and perfecter of his faith.

24:27.799 --> 24:29.541
Perfect means perfect.

24:31.182 --> 24:35.026
Perfect means there is nothing better out there

24:35.554 --> 24:37.696
than him, and this is what Bill believed.

24:39.178 --> 24:45.085
There was nothing out there better than his life with his Jesus.

24:48.889 --> 24:59.642
You know, I might have not won the lottery, but I can say this with complete sincerity that I believe the same thing.

25:01.984 --> 25:03.506
My life is richer

25:04.162 --> 25:07.406
than I ever expect or deserve with my Jesus.

25:12.072 --> 25:16.378
So the message is short today, but that's it.

25:17.039 --> 25:17.940
I'll end it with this.

25:19.682 --> 25:20.884
Why do we come to church?

25:22.546 --> 25:24.228
Because we need to run together.

25:26.612 --> 25:31.538
As a church, we need Jesus lovers in our lives

25:31.714 --> 25:36.241
planting the right seeds in our hearts because the race is long.

25:37.923 --> 25:45.595
So let's encourage each other, love each other, serve each other, and care for each other's needs.

25:47.718 --> 25:50.522
This is an invitation to all, young and old.

25:50.562 --> 25:54.749
Dr. Rudy has his running shoes on.

25:55.089 --> 25:55.730
He's ready.

26:01.122 --> 26:04.306
Avery, you ready?

26:09.213 --> 26:12.157
Tessa, she's ready.

26:12.798 --> 26:14.139
I know it because I see it.

26:15.702 --> 26:17.864
This is the church I come to.

26:21.149 --> 26:22.070
Let's serve together.

26:25.074 --> 26:27.277
Luke 24, 32 says this.

26:29.861 --> 26:30.962
They asked each other.

26:33.058 --> 26:42.371
We're not our hearts burning within us while he talked with us on the road and opened the scriptures to us.

26:46.337 --> 26:48.460
Don't you want your hearts to burn for Jesus?

26:57.793 --> 26:58.995
That's my prayer for today.

27:00.837 --> 27:01.458
I pray

27:02.722 --> 27:10.954
that our hearts burn together when we come to church and open the scripture and run on this road together.

27:12.215 --> 27:16.742
That our hearts burn so bright that others take notice.

27:18.825 --> 27:28.458
That those around us in this valley can walk with Jesus because we run for him.

27:30.461 --> 27:31.282
So let's pray.

27:34.786 --> 27:41.714
Dear Heavenly Father, we are thankful that you are the author and perfecter of our faith.

27:44.097 --> 27:52.767
You make our lives complete, perfect and better than anything else that we might go after outside.

27:52.807 --> 28:02.258
And so Lord, we just pray that you just allow us to take this message and run with it.

28:03.202 --> 28:08.071
Lord, send us your Holy Spirit because without it, this message goes nowhere.

28:08.632 --> 28:14.464
And I pray for each and every one of us here and those online that you just bless us.

28:15.506 --> 28:17.650
Bless us with a faith that allows us to run.

28:19.513 --> 28:23.741
And we thank you now, Lord, and we ask that you just bless this day in Jesus' name.

28:23.761 --> 28:24.082
Amen.

